radiographic_examinations.findings: Tight proximal stenosis and calcifications of the right coronary artery (RCA), stenosis of the midportion of the left anterior descending artery (LAD), and occlusion of the circumflex artery.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Repeat coronary angiogram showed that both grafts were patent but disclosed new tight stenoses upstream and downstream from the LITA-LAD anastomosis and a new tight stenosis upstream from the RSV-RCA anastomosis.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Both grafts were patent, new tight stenoses at the sites of snare application.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: New lesions were located at the sites of snare application after initial surgery.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Satisfactory left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) of 56%.
Evidence of severe left ventricular dysfunction, LVEF was 35%.
